{
  "doc_id": "7711",
  "text": "The mechanical cleaning obtained by the backwash and air scouring seems to be efficient according to the Figure 4 and Table 3 . The suspended solid increases after the backwash which means that the deposit on the surface of the membrane is removed. The removed particles seem to have poor settling characteristics, which affects the efficiency of the removal of the concentrate which has a low SS concentration compared to the SS concentration in the membrane tank immediately after backwash (Table 3) . Different studies from the treatment of wastewater with membranes show that the fouling can be attributed to the SS properties [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , while others have identified EPS concentrations as a major factor [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , and others have shown that the submicron particles below 0.1mm are a main fouling factor (1) immediately before backwash;",
